start.label: make it up as one goes along

examples.en: The evils continuously or intermittently afflict humanity.
What can we do to defend ourselves against continuously rising prices?
The batteries provide enough power for up to five hours of continuous use.
Typical of stress is this feeling of being continuously on the run.
Political union may longer no possible for a country continuously racked by religious disunion.
The album is divided into different tracks, but it is really one continuous song.
